NEWS of MEFISTO software     English Version      Febuary 2023
--------------------------------------------------------------
3 execution modes:
- BATCH + OpenMP:
  Mefisto may be executed by BATCH, without visualization.
  For example, to mesh, type the command
  echo ProjectName; MESHER MeshDataFileName  >ListingOrNot
or
  cd ProjectName | $MEFISTO/pp/ppmail MeshDataFileName
  Attention: 99; {Save and Exit}
  must be the last option in the file MeshDataFileName
  because it is not possible to come back in interative mode.

- Interactive mode:
  with drawings, data by keyboard typing or mouse clicking.
  For example: To execute le MAILLER command, type
  MAILLER  >ListingOrNot

Idem for ELASTICER FLUIDER THERMICER NLSER ... commands
INITIER may be executed in BATCH mode without DataFileName

OPENMP directives have been added in Fortran subroutines and programs.
Don't forget to initialize the environement variable
OMP_NUM_THREADS (processor threads number:12 for Intel Icore 7 )
Cf https://www.ann.jussieu.fr/perronnet/OMPLJLL/OMPLJLL.html

MESHER:
- Improved Option 9 and 19 of volume tetrahedrization
- Improved option 29 with interactive commands to modify
  the 2d or 3d surface mesh from menus and mouse clicks

FLUIDER:
- Under the Boussinesq condition, a computation of the natural convection
  is prposed. With the pressure and velocity, the temperature is computed
  with Taylor-Hood finite elements. Cf testa/recth
- The storage of VELOCITIES+PRESSURES+TEMPERATURES VECTOR at each step
  time may be very large. Now, Each of them is stored on a FILE.
  Every drawing demand asks the time interval to use. Cf testa/d123_r
  ATTENTION: MAIN MEMORY+SWAP may be TOO SMALL!...
  Cf testa/d123_r/d123_r_12_pad123
- A User's updated Manual of Mefisto-FLUIDER is loadable
- Cf https://www.ljll.math.upmc.fr/perronnet/NSROLL/NSROLL.html
- Cf https://www.ljll.math.upmc.fr/perronnet/COVID/COVID_respiration.html
- Cf testa/d123_r/

NLSER:
- Complex solution of the NON-LINEAR SCHRODINGER Equation
  i dU(t,X)/dt -Alfa Laplacian U(t,X) + N(t,|U(t,X)|**2) U(t,X)
  -i OmegaZ ( x dU(t,X)/dy - y dU(t,X)/dx ) = F(t,X)
  Cf the documentation of the initial menu doca/debunlse.
  Cf https://www.ljll.math.upmc.fr/perronnet/NLSE/NLSE.html

$MEFISTO/bin.lnx64:
- The libraries contain subroutines fortran.f95 with OpenMP
  directives and executable on multi-processors as
  Intel Core i7 (12 threads maximum)
- The command ended by .f offers a sequential gfortran
  compilation WITHOUT calls to OpenMP library
  example: $MEFISTO/bin/cbflui gives $MEFISTO/pp/ppflui
  a sequential load module for the command FLUIDER
- The command ended by .f95 offers a MULTI-THREADS gfortran
  compilation with calls to OpenMP library which replace
  the previous compilation
  example: $MEFISTO/bin/cbflui gives $MEFISTO/pp/ppflui
  a multi-threads load module for the command FLUIDER

testa: test files
- d123_r: Mefisto data files to obtain the results of
  https://www.ljll.math.upmc.fr/perronnet/COVID/COVID_respiration.html
- Flow from 0 to 120 seconds of a 2d or 3d fluid of Reynolds
  number 300 around a roll in a box by Brezzi-Fortin (bf) or
  Taylor-Hood (th) finite elements by conjugate gradient:
  rol2dbfcg, rol3dbfcg,  rol2dthcg,  rol3dthcg
- Non Linear Schrodinger Equation tests in testa/nlsgpe

